description:
&lt;p&gt;This is a Full-Time position post based at the Dennis Scott Unit (DSU), Edgware Community Hospital and Elysian Recovery House. It will provide excellent experience of working with people with a wide range of acute metal health problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Barnet HTT works with people who are in mental health crisis and who may require treatment in hospital, but who can be safely and effectively managed in their own home. There is also a 12 bedded Recovery House that forms part of the acute care patient pathway and gives an alternative place of treatment to hospital in situations where home treatment has become untenable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team is undergoing expansion and recruitment into a series of new roles, Social work, OT, Systemic Family Therapist roles and etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a 6 months fixed term post pending Royal College approval to recruit substantively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*Strictly no agencies please&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Asma Batool, Consultant Psychiatrist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;asma.batool2@nhs.net / 020 8702 6582&lt;/p&gt;
